José Aldo da Silva Oliveira Junior -LRB- -LSB- ʒoˈzɛ ˈaldu -RSB- ; born September 9 , 1986 -RRB- is a Brazilian mixed martial artist in the Ultimate Fighting Championship and the UFC Featherweight Champion , currently in his second reign .
He was the fourth and final WEC Featherweight Champion and thus , became the first UFC Featherweight Champion during the UFC/WEC merger .
He is currently a two-time UFC Featherweight Champion , having been promoted from interim champion in the wake of former champion Conor McGregor relinquishing the title on November 27 , 2016 .
He was named Sherdog 's 2009 Fighter of the Year .
He is currently # 5 in official UFC pound-for-pound rankings , having been ranked as high as # 1 in 2015 , and ranked the # 2 featherweight in the world and # 8 pound-for-pound by Sherdog .
In the decade between losses in November 2005 and December 2015 , Aldo was undefeated in 18 fights , before being defeated by Conor McGregor at UFC 194 .
In Sherdog 's 2017 Pound-For-Pound ranking , Aldo was called `` the greatest featherweight in mixed martial arts history . ''